| KAIZEN-02 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-14 | 2026-05-14 | Work-auth constant fields wired from `config/profile.yml` `autosubmit:` section into COMBOBOX_VALUE_HINTS at runtime. `fillRequiredRadioGroups` extended to cover `[role="group"]` containers (Greenhouse work-auth fieldsets). Should unblock Country, City, work-auth radio, visa-sponsorship radio across ~20 stuck applications. |
| TD-10 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-17 | 2026-05-17 | `bat_notes` in last-refresh.json truncated when card-ID list exceeded CLI arg buffer. Fixed: `merge-bat-results.mjs` now writes full per-card detail to `data/bat-run-log.json` and passes a short ≤200-char summary to last-refresh.json. No more data loss on long bat runs. |
| KAIZEN-03 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-17 | 2026-05-17 | Grade C cards accumulating in new-hot drove Freshness score to 0/100. Added `autoArchiveGradeC()` to Kanban: moves Grade C non-seed cards older than 24h from new-hot to cold-backlog column on page load. New `cold-backlog` column added to COLUMNS array. |
| KAIZEN-04 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-17 | 2026-05-17 | `getContainerLabel` couldn't find labels on Greenhouse `<div role="group">` work-auth sections (no `<legend>`, no `aria-labelledby`), causing `fillRequiredRadioGroups` to skip them entirely — root cause of 83% block rate. Fixed: added two new fallback strategies (preceding sibling text scan + first non-interactive child text) so these containers now resolve their labels and get radio-filled. |
| TD-11 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-18 | 2026-05-18 | Country*/City* ARIA combobox fill failing — `fill()` bypasses React event chain, virtual list stays empty. Fixed: replaced `searchInput.fill()` + 400ms with `searchInput.tripleClick()` + `type(value, {delay:80})` + 600ms settle. waitForSelector timeout increased 1500→3000ms. Added retry pass: if no options visible after first attempt, clear and re-type first word only (handles "United States" → "United" seed). Root cause of ~85% block rate. |
| TD-16 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-20 | 2026-05-20 | `auto-submit.mjs` truncated at line 1549 — unterminated template literal; file did not parse. AutoSubmit fully broken for both VM and Windows bat. Reconstructed tail: blocked-fields log + submit button handler + try/catch/finally + `main()` export. `node --check` clean. |
| KAIZEN-GE | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-20 | 2026-05-20 | FORTUNE_500 set in Kanban used pre-2024 name "general electric"; GE Aerospace and GE Vernova not recognized → B-grade cards incorrectly routed to SuS gate. Added `'ge aerospace'` and `'ge vernova'` to FORTUNE_500 set. |
| KAIZEN-BAT | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-20 | 2026-05-20 | Windows bat (JobPulse-AutoSubmit) not firing — `bat_ran_at: null`. Root cause: Task Scheduler registration stale/missing after session gap. Created `register-all-tasks.bat` — registers both `CoworkLaunch-555am` and `JobPulse-AutoSubmit`, and programmatically enables WakeToRun on both via PowerShell COM. Run once as Administrator to fix. |
| TD-17 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-20 | 2026-05-20 | `dedup-tracker.mjs` truncated at git HEAD (line 229, missing `writeFileSync` tail). Also: `roleMatch()` had `overlap.length >= 2` hard gate — after ROLE_STOPWORDS strips "manager", single-word titles never matched → dupes not caught. Fixed: `Math.min(2, smaller)` floor, restored writeFileSync tail. |
| TD-18 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-21 | 2026-05-21 | `searchInput.tripleClick()` called on `ElementHandle` (from `page.$()`) — method only exists on `Locator`. Crashed 17/44 bat cards (38.6%) with `TypeError: searchInput.tripleClick is not a function`. Fixed: replaced all `.tripleClick()` calls with `.click({clickCount: 3})` which works on both ElementHandle and Locator. |
| KAIZEN-F500-GATE | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-21 | 2026-05-21 | `auto-submit.mjs` SuS gate ignored FORTUNE_500 set — only checked `sus-db.confirmed[]`. GE Aerospace and Humana landed in SuS instead of auto-submitting. Fixed: added `FORTUNE_500` set to `auto-submit.mjs` (mirrors Kanban), added pre-SuS `isF500` check — F500 companies bypass SuS gate entirely. Slug forms added (`geaerospace`, `gevernova`, etc.) to handle Workday URL normalization. |
| KAIZEN-05 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-21 | 2026-05-21 | Added `--confirm-f500` batch CLI command. Reads sus-db, auto-confirms all entries whose company name matches FORTUNE_500 set. Run: `node auto-submit.mjs --confirm-f500`. Ran successfully: confirmed geaerospace ×3, humana, medtronic, philips. |
| TD-19 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-22 | 2026-05-21 | Stripe `no-submit-button` — 4 cards stuck (live-32/33/50/51). `absolute_url` from Greenhouse API returned `stripe.com/jobs/search?gh_jid=X` (search page, no submit button). Fixed: `normalizeStripeUrl()` added to `scan.mjs` `parseGreenhouse()` — converts to `stripe.com/jobs/listing/{title-slug}/{id}` at scan time. 4 existing Kanban cards patched with correct listing URLs. |
| KAIZEN-CONFIRM | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-21 | 2026-05-21 | `auto-submit.mjs` exited 0 after button click alone — no ATS confirmation verified. "Submitted" count was meaningless (7 unconfirmed bat-run cards). Fixed: replaced 2500ms wait + exit-0 with 8s confirmation signal gate: checks URL change, `/confirmation\|/success\|/thank-you` path, and success-text regex. No signal after 8s → exit 3 with `blocked_fields:['no-confirmation-signal']`. Company confirmation email = real submission; this is the closest in-process proxy. |
| KAIZEN-KANBAN-SOT | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-21 | 2026-05-21 | 8am report derived submitted count from `last-refresh.json` alone (no ground truth). Fixed: added `submitted` Kanban column (id:`submitted`, "Auto-Confirmed ✅") — cards moved there by `auto-submit.mjs` only after ATS confirmation signal. Added `moveKanbanCard(url,'submitted')` call on exit-0 path. 8am SKILL Step 6 + Step 10 updated: Kanban `submitted` column count is authoritative; `last-refresh.json` is cross-checked and discrepancies flagged. `new-fresh` column relabeled "Applied (Manual/Pipeline)" to clarify the two lanes. |
| KAIZEN-F500-MISSING | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-22 | 2026-05-22 | Motorola Solutions, Medtronic, Philips, T-Mobile were in `sus-db.confirmed[]` but absent from the `FORTUNE_500` set in both `auto-submit.mjs` and `kanban.html`. These are real Fortune 500 companies — missing from the set caused them to route to SuS instead of auto-submitting. Fixed: added display names + slug forms (`motorolasolutions`, `tmobile`, `medtronic`, `philips`) to both sets. |
| KAIZEN-ATOMIC-WRITE | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-22 | 2026-05-22 | Non-atomic JSON writes across `auto-submit.mjs` (`saveJson`), `write-refresh-status.mjs`, and `linkedin-dm.mjs` (`saveLog`) caused truncation/NUL-byte corruption when two writers collided (root cause of the 2026-05-22 P1 incident). Fixed: all three now use write-to-`.tmp`-then-`renameSync` — atomic on all POSIX/NTFS filesystems. |
| KAIZEN-BAT-RESCHEDULE | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-22 | 2026-05-22 | JobPulse-AutoSubmit bat fired at 6:10am, colliding with the 6am cloud refresh still running (both writing to the same JSON DBs in the same ~3-minute window). Moved bat to 6:45am in `register-all-tasks.bat`. Run `register-all-tasks.bat` as Administrator to apply. |
| KAIZEN-CREDS-ENV | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-22 | 2026-05-22 | LinkedIn and Workday credentials stored as plaintext in `config/profile.yml`. Added env var support to `auto-submit.mjs` (`WORKDAY_EMAIL`, `WORKDAY_PASSWORD`) and `linkedin-dm.mjs` (`LINKEDIN_EMAIL`, `LINKEDIN_PASSWORD`). Env vars take precedence; profile.yml is fallback. Created `set-credentials.bat` for one-time Windows env var setup (no admin required). |
| KAIZEN-GE-LOGISTICS | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-22 | 2026-05-22 | GE Aerospace logistics cards live-54/55/56 graded B, sitting in AutoSubmit lane. JD analysis confirmed they require Oracle WMS specialist expertise (8+ years) — outside Rahil's background. Re-graded B→C and moved to `cold-backlog` in Kanban. Removed from AutoSubmit queue. |
| KAIZEN-ALREADY-APPLIED | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-22 | 2026-05-22 | AutoSubmit re-visited Ashby cards for Datatonic, Acorns, Deepgram, SpruceID (already applied in prior runs). Ashby showed "already applied" status pages containing phrases like "Your application was submitted on [date]" — the confirmation-signal regex false-positived, counting them as new submissions. No emails received because no new applications were sent. Fixed: (1) "already applied" exclusion check fires BEFORE success regex in confirmation gate — exit 3 with `already-applied` flag; (2) pre-submission URL dedup check reads applications.md and skips cards already marked Applied/Submitted before launching browser. 4 Kanban cards moved back from `submitted` → `new-fresh`. |
| KAIZEN-06 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-23 | 2026-05-23 | `build-autosubmit-queue.mjs` only picked up `new-hot` cards (tier-1 F500). `autosubmit-ready` whitelist column (tier-2, user-moved) was silently ignored — whitelist flow was fully broken. Fixed: unioned both columns with dedup; output now reports tier-1/tier-2 counts. |
| TD-20 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-23 | 2026-05-23 | Raytheon/RTX uses shared Workday tenant `globalhr` — hostname prefix extracted by `extractCompanyFromUrl` was `globalhr`, not recognized by FORTUNE_500 gate → routed to SuS. Fixed: `WORKDAY_TENANT_ALIASES` map added to `auto-submit.mjs`; `extractCompanyFromUrl` resolves known tenant slugs to canonical company names before returning. |
| TD-21 | ✅ RESOLVED 2026-05-23 | 2026-05-23 | Workday no-submit-button blocked 100% of F500 Workday bat cards. Root causes: (1) static UA string triggering bot-detection on Cloudflare layer; (2) submit button lazy-renders after scroll — query fired before DOM element existed. Fixed: randomized UA pool (5 Chrome/Win+Mac variants) in browser context; double scroll-to-bottom + 3s settle added to `handleWorkday()` before returning. NOTE: the scroll-settle portion was a misdiagnosis — see TD-23. UA-pool change retained. |
| TD-22 | ✅ FIXED 2026-05-24 (pending 6:45am bat verify) | 2026-05-24 | F500 AutoSubmit lane 15/15 blocked in the 2026-05-23 bat. Root cause for 8/15 cards: Greenhouse jobs injected as company marketing-wrapper URLs (`stripe.com/jobs/listing/...`, `databricks.com/...?gh_jid=...`) that carry the job id but render a marketing page with no application form — `detectATS` returned `'unknown'`, no platform handler ran, stalled at `no-submit-button`. Confirmed via `data/ats-pattern-hits.json` (`"ats":"unknown"`). Fixed in `auto-submit.mjs`: new `canonicalizeApplyUrl()` rewrites wrappers to `job-boards.greenhouse.io/{board}/jobs/{id}` before detection; `detectATS` now recognizes `gh_jid` + Stripe listing URLs. URL-transform logic unit-tested (Stripe/Databricks/Duolingo → correct board URLs). |
| TD-23 | ✅ FIXED 2026-05-24 (pending 6:45am bat verify) | 2026-05-24 | Workday F500 cards (7/15: humana, medtronic, philips, tmobile, motorola×2, cvshealth) blocked `no-submit-button`. Root cause: `handleWorkday` checked the Sign In wall only BEFORE the Apply click; Workday routes Apply → an auth page, so the wall was never handled and the wizard loop ran on the login page (TD-21's scroll-settle was the wrong fix — no button to lazy-render, the script was stranded on an auth page). Fixed: extracted `tryWorkdayLogin()` helper, now called pre- AND post-Apply. CAVEAT: each Workday tenant is a separate account — cross-tenant hands-off still needs a pre-created account per F500 Workday tenant. See escalation. |